author: CARSON, California
title: Honduras gets CONCACAF semifinals spot
text: CARSON, California — Antony Lozano and Alberth Elis scored to help Honduras beat Costa Rica 2-0 Sunday, and Honduras got a spot in the semifinals in CONCACAF qualifying for the 2016 Rio Olympics when Mexico beat Haiti. Honduras and Mexico, a 1-0 winner in the second game of the doubleheader, is 2-0 in Group B, while Costa Rica and Haiti are 0-2. Seeking its third straight berth in the Olympics and fourth overall, Honduras will finish the round robin Wednesday night against Mexico in Commerce City, Colorado, with the winner getting the top spot from the group in the Oct. 10 semifinals in Sandy, Utah. On Friday, Honduras beat Haiti 1-0, and Mexico topped Costa Rica 4-0. — AP
